The paper proposes a new framework for manifold denoising based on processing in the graph Fourier frequency domain, which involves graph-based signal processing techniques. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Among these, cs.IT and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as the paper deals with signal processing and image denoising, respectively. The other categories are also possible, as the paper involves numerical methods and graph-based analysis, which are relevant to these sub-fields.
